o Invert the keys and values in a hash:
<pre>
#!/usr/bin/env perl

use 5.018;

# -----------------------------

my(%hash) = (A => 1, B => 2, C => 3);

say 'Keys hash:   ', join(', ', sort keys %hash);
say 'Values hash: ', join(', ', sort values %hash);
say;

my(%invert);

# RHS must be an array.

@invert{@{[sort values %hash]} } = sort keys %hash;

say 'Keys invert:   ', join(', ', sort keys %invert);
say 'Values invert: ', join(', ', sort values %invert);
</pre>

o Syntax::Keyword::Dynamically:
- Dynamically change the value of a variable
- Effectively:
{
   my $old = $VAR;
   $VAR = "new value";

   ...

   $VAR = $old;
}
- Except that the old value will also be restored in the case of exceptions, goto, next/last/redo or similar ways to leave the controlling block scope.
